#: ../../source/overview.rst:7
#: d9fb076e16fd44c58da817dc70077e0c
msgid "The Security Force Monitor works to make police, military and other security forces around the world more transparent and accountable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:9
#: 263a2d056ff24585bd2e79f6a3edce46
msgid "Human rights researchers, journalists, advocates, litigators and others engaged in making security forces accountable face a common problem – a lack of clear, detailed information on those forces. Often, answering even simple questions can be difficult:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:11
#: 48a96e3a99604e65a232b3f8e7d39f0a
msgid "Who is in charge of the specialized anti-riot police unit?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:12
#: 8bd35aeadccb4058bf32d44c01ef270c
msgid "What army unit has jurisdiction over what areas?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:13
#: be848e733ffa4fc4939f9bd668826790
msgid "Where did this commander previously serve?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:14
#: 3175ac79d2c74bea90db99056997926d
msgid "When was a particular police unit based in a specific city?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:16
#: 591b45d8486940d7870d4670e5f597e0
msgid "There is a vast amount of public information on security forces around the world, but it is unstructured and scattered among a wide variety of sources, making it prohibitively costly for those engaged in public interest work to understand the security forces of a particular country."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:18
#: c7714be475bb406cba410c2c7ae03a46
msgid "The Security Force Monitor aims to solve this problem and aid those working to make police, military and other security forces accountable. The Monitor analyzes and compiles public information to provide data on: the command hierarchy, location, areas of operation, commanders and the other linkages between units – all tracked through time. The Monitor’s mission and technical offerings have been developed to serve, and in consultation with, a wide range of civil society efforts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:20
#: 290028c634f94e5c9d7dcfe383f8f0d8
msgid "The Security Force Monitor is a project of the `Columbia Law School Human Rights Institute <http://www.law.columbia.edu/human-rights-institute>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:22
#: 541c51c43f9945baaf6b2295b273b662
msgid "`More information about Security Force Monitor <https://securityforcemonitor.org>`__ can be found on our website."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:25
#: 739eda9a1e8146359043d7fa057b4682
msgid "About this Research Handbook"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:27
#: 5b6f530c63304cd4831fce21e5b2ade1
msgid "This Research Handbook is a guide to investigating the structure, personnel, infrastructure, operations and connections to human rights abuses of security forces around the world. It provides detailed information  about the methods, data and tools used by Security Force Monitor to do this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:29
#: 92b5a88dd37844f68d0bd08afb382adc
msgid "The Research Handbook has three sections:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:31
#: 0ae6f86a692a40cbb06c6359936f129b
msgid "**WhoWasInCommand.com User Guide**: The data created by Security Force Monitor is published online at https://WhoWasInCommand.com, a purpose-built platform with powerful search functions, clean and interactive views of the organizational structure, command of personnel and chains of command, and the geographical footprint of security forces in many countries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:32
#: 37de1f5c64fc4a9f837a13e152a5ec3c
msgid "**Methodology**: Security Force Monitor has a four phase approach to researching a country's security forces. This section outlines our process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:33
#: 25546358423e4f29b4872f29e8b0bded
msgid "**Data Model**: this section describes the way that Security Force Monitor structures the data it collects and the steps taken to ensure data integrity. In this section, we also provide detailed documentation about the standard data collection formats and fields that we use to organize our research and store data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:35
#: 02d49d8482e446248c962c766fa72feb
msgid "the :doc:`persons` and :doc:`persons_extra` formats are used to capture data about persons, their ranks and roles within security forces, information about their online presence and how they look and sound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:37
#: 506f209707f7414e8f4e6ab738235323
msgid "the :doc:`units` format is used to stored data about the organizational structure of a security force, its physical infrastructure and its areas areas of operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:39
#: 46c1dc82b4834ebd8353a73875ef1614
msgid "the :doc:`incidents` format is used to store data about human rights abuses specific units or persons from security forces are alleged to have committed."
msgstr ""

